docs.abstract: One new plan offers video streaming only, while another offers full Prime benefits. Both cost more than annual subscribers pay.
docs.snippet: One new plan offers video streaming only, while another offers full Prime benefits. Both cost more than annual subscribers pay.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon is introducing new options to subscribe to its Prime membership service on a monthly basis, a change that could make the company’s video service a tougher competitor to Netflix.

headline.main: Amazon Challenges Netflix by Opening Prime to Monthly Subscribers
headline.print_headline: Amazon Opens Prime to Monthly Subscriptions in Move to Challenge Netflix

docs.abstract: Season 2 of this Amazon Prime show picks up with its stars expecting a baby a couple of years after an unplanned pregnancy led, eventually, to romance.

docs.lead_paragraph: Love is a mess. It’s awkward and clumsy and can lead to the uncomfortable gestation of a small human.

headline.main: ‘Catastrophe’ Adds a New Wrinkle to Its Ribald Love Story: Children

docs.abstract: The new $289 Kindle Oasis e-reader has an asymmetrical shape meant to mimic a book, and includes a case with a battery that extends charge time.

docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — When Amazon introduced Kindle, its pioneering e-reader, in 2007, society was on the cusp of being changed by mobile devices.

headline.main: Kindle Oasis From Amazon Promises ‘Months and Months’ of Battery Life
headline.print_headline: New Kindle Keeps the Focus on Reading

docs.abstract: This economics of tiny things demonstrates the global power of the few companies, including Amazon, Microsoft and Google, that can make fortunes from the small.
docs.snippet: This economics of tiny things demonstrates the global power of the few companies, including Amazon, Microsoft and Google, that can make fortunes from the small.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Imagine building an enormous beach resort, maybe the best in the world. Instead of renting the rooms, you charge guests based on the grains of sand they touch. You charge very little per grain, but if they lie on enough of them, it adds up.

headline.main: Billing by Millionths of Pennies, Cloud Computing’s Giants Take In Billions
headline.print_headline: Billing by Millionths of Pennies, Cloud Computing Giants Make Billions

docs.abstract: Amazon made a profit of $513 million in its most recent quarter, and its Amazon Web Services was the star of the show.
docs.snippet: Amazon made a profit of $513 million in its most recent quarter, and its Amazon Web Services was the star of the show.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ten years ago last March, Amazon started the era of renting data storage and computing over the Internet, what is now known as cloud computing. On Thursday, Amazon showed how critical it is to the retailer’s future.

headline.main: Cloud Services Show Their Value in Earnings Reports
